22/07/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- On Monday (21 July), the EU foreign ministers decided to extend the Concordia mission in Macedonia until 15 December. The mandate of the 380 troops from 27 countries will remain unchanged. The decision was made at the request of the Macedonian government. President Boris Trajkovski has asked that Concordia be transformed into a police mission after the extended mandate expires. (Dnevnik, Makfax - 22/07/03; AFP, MIA - 21/07/03)
